penalties.bareActText:
33. (1) If the Board determines, after conducting an inquiry, that a person has failed to comply with the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder, it may, after giving such person a reasonable opportunity of being heard, impose such penalty as it thinks fit.

(2) The Board may impose a penalty which may extend to—
(a) two hundred crore rupees, if the person has failed to fulfill the obligations in relation to children or Significant Data Fiduciary under this Act;
(b) two hundred crore rupees, if the person has failed to notify the Board and each affected Data Principal, of a personal data breach;
(c) two hundred crore rupees, if the person has failed to comply with the directions issued by the Board;
(d) ten thousand rupees, for each instance of failure to comply with any other provision of this Act or the rules made thereunder.

(3) While determining the penalty under sub-section (1), the Board shall have regard to—
(a) the nature, gravity and duration of the breach;
(b) the type and nature of personal data affected;
(c) repetitive nature of the breach;
(d) whether the breach was intentional or negligent.

